### Describe the problem
Artifact repository with subdirectories, UI fails to find node since the node doesn't exist in the root artifact 'children' object.  The node exists in the 'children' property of the subdirectory node. Always throws Error("Can't file child") when clicking on the file in preview tree window.

mlflow.log_artifacts("/absolute/path/to/model/dir")

Directory structure (model):
++file1.txt
++file2.txt
++subdirectory
++++file3.txt     <<<< click here in Preview cause Error on run detail screen

static findChild(node, path) {
    const parts = path.split('/');
    let ret = node;
    parts.forEach((part) => {
      if (ret.children && ret.children[part] !== undefined) {   << only searches root node.children
        ret = ret.children[part];
      } else {
        throw new Error("Can't find child.");
      }
    });
    return ret;
  }

### Code to reproduce issue
Provide a reproducible test case that is the bare minimum necessary to generate the problem.

### Other info / logs
Include any logs or source code that would be helpful to diagnose the problem. If including tracebacks,
please include the full traceback. Large logs and files should be attached.
